0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "The " }{TEXT 259 16 "Binomial Theo
rem" }{TEXT -1 66 " gives a formula for finding the coefficients of th
e expansion of " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)^n;" "6#),&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&%\"
nG" }{TEXT -1 10 "  for any " }{TEXT 267 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 53 ".  It is \+
relatively obvious that the coefficient of  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "a^(n-k)*
b^k;" "6#*&)%\"aG,&%\"nG\"\"\"%\"kG!\"\"F()%\"bGF)F(" }{TEXT -1 19 "  \+
for any value of " }{TEXT 268 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 11 " from 0 to " }{TEXT 
269 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 46 " is given by the number of ways we can choose \+
" }{TEXT 270 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 8 " of the " }{TEXT 294 1 "b" }{TEXT -1 
12 "'s from the " }{TEXT 271 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 1 " " }{TEXT 295 1 "b" }
{TEXT -1 20 "'s in the expansion " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)*(a+b)" "6#*&,
&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&F&,&F%F&F'F&F&" }{TEXT -1 7 " ....( " }{XPPEDIT 18 
0 "(a+b)" "6#,&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF%" }{TEXT -1 5 " ),  " }{TEXT 272 1 "n
" }{TEXT -1 41 " times .   The number of combinations of " }{TEXT 273 
1 "n" }{TEXT -1 18 " objects choosing " }{TEXT 274 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 12 
" at a time, " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "nCk" "6#%$nCkG" }{TEXT -1 27 ", is give
n by the formula  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "nCk=n!/(k!*(n-k)!)" "6#/%$nCkG*&-%
*factorialG6#%\"nG\"\"\"*&-F'6#%\"kGF*-F'6#,&F)F*F.!\"\"F*F2" }{TEXT 
-1 2 " ." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 261 
10 "State the " }{TEXT 260 16 "Binomial Theorem" }{TEXT -1 1 " " }
{TEXT 275 31 "and use Maple to demonstrate it" }{TEXT -1 1 "." }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 492 "In algebra, a formula for expansion of t
he binomial (x + y) raised to any positive integer power.\n\nA simple \+
case is the expansion of (x + y)2, which is x2 + 2xy + y2. In general,
 the expression (x + y)n expands to the sum of (n + 1)terms in which t
he power of x decreases from n to 0 while the power of y increases fro
m 0 to n in successive terms. The terms can be represented in factoria
l notation by the expression [n!/((n ? r)!r!)]xn ? ryr in which r take
s on integer values from 0 to n.\n\n" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 11 "g:=(x+y)^8;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%\"gG
*$),&%\"xG\"\"\"%\"yGF)\"\")F)" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 
1 0 10 "expand(g);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,4*$)%\"xG\"\")
\"\"\"F(*(F'F()F&\"\"(F(%\"yGF(F(*(\"#GF()F&\"\"'F()F,\"\"#F(F(*(\"#cF
()F&\"\"&F()F,\"\"$F(F(*(\"#qF()F&\"\"%F()F,F<F(F(*(F4F()F&F8F()F,F6F(
F(*(F.F()F&F2F()F,F0F(F(*(F'F(F&F()F,F+F(F(*$)F,F'F(F(" }}}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 8 "Compute " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "sum(binomial(n,k),k=0..n)" 
"6#-%$sumG6$-%)binomialG6$%\"nG%\"kG/F*;\"\"!F)" }{TEXT -1 34 "  for n
=1 to 10.  Here the symbol " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "Sigma;" "6#%&SigmaG" }
{TEXT -1 70 " (Greek letter Sigma) stands for sum.   (See the workshee
t SumSeq.mws)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 
0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 75 "for i from 1 to 10\ndo Sum(binomial(i,k),k=0..i)
=\nsum(binomial(i,k),k=0..i);" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 3 "od;
" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#/-%$SumG6$-%)binomialG6$\"\"\"%\"k
G/F+;\"\"!F*\"\"#" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#/-%$SumG6$-%)bino
mialG6$\"\"#%\"kG/F+;\"\"!F*\"\"%" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#/
-%$SumG6$-%)binomialG6$\"\"$%\"kG/F+;\"\"!F*\"\")" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#/-%$SumG6$-%)binomialG6$\"\"%%\"kG/F+;\"\"!F*\"#;" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#/-%$SumG6$-%)binomialG6$\"\"&%\"kG/F+;
\"\"!F*\"#K" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#/-%$SumG6$-%)binomialG6
