0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 258 59 "What general formula do the ab
ove calculations in  suggest?" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 58 "I know t
hat each answer is two times the one before....2x?" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 388 "2.  Pascal's Triangle.  \+
Recall the definition of Pascal's Triangle.   Use Maple to construct t
he first 10 rows of Pascal's Triangle. (The trick will be to get the c
oefficients to occur in the correct order.  The Maple command for gene
rating a sequence might be helpful. It is   seq(expression(i),i=m..n);
   where expression(i) is an expression with index i and m..n is a ran
ge of numbers." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 3 "   " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 ">
 " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 56 "for n from 0 to 9\ndo\nseq(coeff((a+1)^n,a,p)
,p=0..n);\nod;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#\"\"\"" }}{PARA 11 "
" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"\"F#" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6%\"\"
\"\"\"#F#" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6&\"\"\"\"\"$F$F#" }}{PARA 
